knx-installer (0.4.1.23) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Kel Modderman ]
  * Remove system_install_keymap, that is handled during live-mode now.
  * reverted changes done concerning groot/root device
  * Massive cleanup of install-tools.bm.
    - remove anthing Kanotix/Knoppix specific
    - system_install_i18n, system_setup_kdm, system_add_hd_autoconfig,
      system_add_services, system_fix_menus all dissolved or removed
  * Create service whitelist (array), and filter out unwanted services that
    have been installed in the chroot, and are thus active by default. This
    means we can remove the hardcoded sequnce numbers associated with
    recreating/scripting entire boot process ourselves (if it works).

  [ Stefan Lippers-Hollmann ]
  * don't install templates/.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 23 Jan 2007 16:39:52 +0100

knx-installer (0.4.1.22) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Kel Modderman ]
  * Remove very ugly hack to kdesktoprc, don't hide unmounted hdd's, and
    certainly do not muck around with /etc/skel.
  * Remove commented out virtual filesystem from fstab template, allow init
    scripts (mountkernfs.sh, mountdevsubfs.sh) to hide these from the user.
  * Remove hacks to icon files, swapping sudo for kdesu and so on.
  * Don't do install-keymap when one already exists.
  * Remove Knoppix.desktop hack, do we really want to continue supporting that
    stuff?
  * Remove reference to 855resolution, its obsolete by now.
  * Move ipw3945d detection to system_add_services().
  * filter some uninteresting lines on menu.lst that can be confusing

  [ Stefan Lippers-Hollmann ]
  * adapt sidux-installer to call install-gui.
  * revert to standard debian .bashrc.

